@F forget.flow v1.0 2026-01-13
= deletion > archiving â€” releasing what no longer serves

intent
  remove "understanding" by topic
  enforce "ownership" (can only forget own memories unless --all)
  verify "intent" (explicit command)

logic
  input: topic_pattern
  scope: sys_understanding
  
  process
    1. find memories matching topic_pattern
    2. check ownership
       if creator == me: mark for delete
       if --all flag: mark for delete
       else: skip
    3. execute delete
    4. report count

commands
  py forget <topic>          | forget my understanding
  py forget <topic> --all    | forget everyone's understanding

integration
  SovereignAgent (auth, memory)
  UnifiedMemory (delete)
